{{Quote|The primary function of the New Republic Security Force shall be the maintenance of lawful order through the elimination of all agents, foreign and domestic, seeking to undermine the lawful authority of the New Republic.|Excerpt from the preamble of the NRSF charter|<ref name="GG11:CO" />}}
The '''New Republic Security Force (NRSF)''' or '''New Republic Security''', was the primary [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|law enforcement]] and [[Spy/Legends|counter-intelligence]] agency for the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] government. The NRSF was formed in [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]] in the aftermath of the New Republic's [[Liberation of Coruscant (Galactic Civil War)|seizure]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. It was designed to fill the role of its Imperial counterpart, the [[Sector Ranger/Legends|Sector Rangers]], and many NRSF [[Agent/Legends|agents]] were former Sector Rangers. The NRSF was concerned primarily with maintaining civil order by investigating corruption, [[Slavery/Legends|slavery]] and organized crime, capturing [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial spies]] within the New Republic government, and protecting and investigating abuses of the civil rights of New Republic citizens. The NRSF continued with these functions until the New Republic was dissolved and replaced by the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]] in [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]].

==Overview==
{{Quote|As the maintenance of peace can only be ensured when the rights of all sentient beings, regardless of species, origin, or philosophy, are respected, agents of the New Republic Security Force shall dedicate themselves to safeguarding those rights, and to bring to justice any and all violators, wherever they may be found.|Excerpt from the preamble of the NRSF charter|<ref name="GG11:CO" />}}
[[File:NRSF_agent.jpg|thumb|left|140px|An NRSF agent]]
The New Republic Security Force was chartered as the primary [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|law enforcement agency]] within the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and designed with the same function in mind as their counterpart in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], the [[Sector Ranger/Legends|Sector Rangers]]. NRSF [[Agent/Legends|agents]] held dual roles as [[Police officer/Legends|police officers]], enforcing the New Republic's laws to ensure civil order, and as [[Spy/Legends|counter-intelligence]] operatives, preventing infiltration by [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial spies]] and [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorists]]. Despite a vast territory to police and insufficient manpower, NRSF agents were some of the best police officers in the New Republic. Deeply motivated and highly trained, many were former Sector Rangers and had a vast array of skills to call upon. When working to investigate corruption, criminal syndicates, or possible Imperial activity, NRSF agents would conduct deep covert missions to discover the criminals or spies. Due to the strains on the New Republic government, NRSF agents were given limited judiciary powers should the situation demand it.<ref name="GG11:CO" />

In its efforts to enforce New Republic laws, the NRSF focused on maintaining general civil order by combating organized crime, [[Slavery/Legends|slavery]], and criminal corruption. They also were specifically entrusted with protecting the basic rights of New Republic citizens which in practice could involve protecting persons against anything from a [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord's]] enforcers to [[Stormtrooper/Legends|Imperial stormtroopers]]. Additionally, NRSF agents would assist local police with their investigations if the criminals fled from the local jurisdiction or if the case was beyond the means of the local police to investigate properly. However, assistance and/or interference by the NRSF was not always appreciated.<ref name="GG11:CO" />

The second major role for the NRSF was serving as the New Republic's counter-intelligence agency. Specifically, it was to prevent the government from being infiltrated by spies from the Galactic Empire, conduct terrorist activities. In this regard, the NRSF had overlapping duties with its larger intelligence counterpart, the [[New Republic Intelligence Service]] (NRI).<ref name="GG11:CO" /> Likewise, the NRI performed similar functions as the NRSF: tracking the activities of criminals, [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]], and terrorists.<ref name="GoI" /> As the NRSF had significantly fewer personnel<ref name="GG11:CO" /> and the NRI was in its early [[Standard year/Legends|years]] formerly a part of the [[New Republic Defense Force/Legends|New Republic military]],<ref name="GoI" /> the NRSF focused more on law enforcement actions against criminal groups<ref name="GG11:CO" /> while the NRI worked to provide intelligence with a military focus.<ref name="GoI" />

==History==
The New Republic Security Force had its origins in the Imperial Sector Rangers. One of the oldest law enforcement agencies in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], the Sector Rangers had been formed since the early days of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and had remained little changed with the [[Declaration of a New Order|formation]] of the Galactic Empire. In [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]] the New Republic [[Liberation of Coruscant (Galactic Civil War)|captured]] the galactic [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], establishing itself as the dominate galactic government. While local and planetary police forces had been left largely in place, the New Republic government saw the need for a law enforcement service dedicated to enforcing its common laws. The NRSF was created with the charter of ensuring civil order by enforcing the New Republic's laws, preventing infiltration by enemy agents, and protecting the civil rights of all sentient citizens of the New Republic. Though overall politically the NRSF and the Sector Rangers were at opposite ends, the Rangers had stayed separate from the general [[Imperialization/Legends|Imperialization]] of the galaxy. As such, the NRSF had no qualms about accepting them into their ranks and most NRSF agents were former Sector Rangers.<ref name="GoI" />

[[General/Legends|General]] [[Airen Cracken/Legends|Airen Cracken]], [[Director of New Republic Intelligence]], was tasked with responsibility of forming the NRSF. He established its headquarters on Coruscant and set about organizing the new agency. It was hoped that the NRSF could help bring order to Coruscant in the absence of the dissolved [[Coruscant Guard/Legends|Coruscant Guard]], and the command structure of the [[Coruscant Security Force/Legends|Coruscant Security Force]] along with the Security Force's Imperial [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] contingent. However, the NRSF was too young and too small to have any immediate effect.<ref name="X-W:TKT" /> Shortly after its formation, [[Myleena Dystra]] joined the NRSF. She was involved in two separate [[Lightfight|fights]] and was injured both times. The second incident was nearly fatal.<ref name="H&R">''[[Heroes & Rogues]]''</ref> At some point, NRSF Agent [[Oollj]] was seriously injured while trying to stop the theft of [[Meleenium/Legends|Meleenium]] from the [[Qua'Tahc]] mines on [[Af'El/Legends|Af'El]].<ref name="SWAJ10">[[Star Wars Adventure Journal 10|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 10]]</ref> The NRSF continued operations until the New Republic was dissolved and replaced by the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]] in [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]].<ref name="TNJO:DW" />

